   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Annual Output Results</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Indicator-based reporting adopted by 3 countries out of 3 and institutional framework of BS monitoring/data collection improved
2 Common methodology for marine environmental assessment based on EU WFD and MSFD developed and submitted to national authorities and National integrated monitoring programmes proposed in line with MSFD principles; amount of environmental data collated in national and regional databases increased by minimum 10% and 30%, respectively; and environmental data collected by the project beneficiary countries cover 60% of the MSFD list of GES indicators
3. Usage of harmonized SOPs, QC/QA and DQC manuals tested by means of questionnaires and field testing (pass marks &gt; 60%), a number of trainings and harmonization workshops organized 
4. Comparability of data enhanced (measured by the common methodologies of sampling, sample processing and data management applied), a number of cruises coordinated with EMBLAS-II (national and regional) taking into consideration the methodologies and new parameters recommended by the project 
5. Availability of data leveled with accessibility, provisions for further maintenance &amp; development of BSIS prepared and inter-operability of the Black Sea WQ data base with other regional and European databases established
6. Further development of EMBLAS visibility &#x2013; update of the Dissemination strategy focused on knowledge management and public awareness, website extended, publication disseminated.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2014">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Bucharest convention and other agreements, EU  Marine Strategy (MSFD) and Water Framework Directive (WFD) existing, countries need to comply with their reporting requirements, activities initiated to improve the indicator-based reporting of the Black Sea Commission, harmonization process for water quality (WQ) and good environmental status (GES) assessment initiated &#x2013; within EMBLAS-I (project preparatory phase)
2. Preparatory activities carried out in EMBLAS-I to support implementation of MSFD- and WFD-compliant biological and chemical monitoring programmes  and National revised monitoring programs drafted, further revision needed
3. Network of Black Sea reference laboratories exists, capacity assessment and further improvement is needed, including implementation of Quality Assurance/Quality Control schemes (QA/QC), standard operational procedures adhering to ISO 17025 (SoPs) and Data Quality Control (DQC). Training Programme available and initial training organized.
4. Framework methodology for Joint Black Sea Surveys prepared to facilitate organizations of monitoring cruises, coordination with cruises under other EU funded projects needs to be ensured
5. Black Sea Water Quality Database developed as a first prototype during EMBLAS I, but not as web-based system &#x2013; a guide for nourishing the database available and an online  training organized, the web portal prototype for the Black Sea Information System (BSIS) was designed and tested. Further testing and development is needed.
6. Dissemination strategy has been prepared for the EMBLAS I, including basic visibility products (website, information leaflet, logo, etc.)</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2018-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2018-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2, 4 Scientific Report from the Black Sea Surveys
5. Finalized uploads of data from the BS surveys 2016 and 2017 to the BS Water Quality Databases
7. Final Donor Report and operational closure of the project.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2, 4 Scientific Reports from the Black Sea Surveys 2017 and from National Pilot Monitoring Studies - 12 months program
5. Uploads of all data from surveys into upgraded BS WQD completed
7. Final Donor Report submitted to EC DG NEAR</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
